<p>Fig. <a href="#fig:vadd-graph-polygon">2</a> (right) show the difference of this method from the previous one. The start point of vector $\vec{r}_2$ is put to the end point of vector $\vec{r}_1$ and the result is from start point of the first vector to the end point of the last vector. The given example of addition of two vectors does not really show the difference between this two methods. It requires more vectors to show the advantage of the second method compared the first one.</p>

